snippet.textDisplay: I'm a fan of Brad, and Brad and Eric, but literally came here to see if Brad addresses the issue of his mislabeled products on here. As a vegan I had plans to buy products after the festive period when I have nothing else to pay out for, based on the labelling of it being vegan, as I choose to live a vegan lifestyle. Had I bought it then found out actually it has crushed beetles in, I wouldn't be happy that I'd paid for something that goes against my moral ethic code and would want the item to be returned as I wouldn't use it and would expect a refund. Just the way glossier addressed their mislabelling and actually contacted customers as the mascara was being shipped and refunded all customers before they even received the product.
